Install GRUB2 to the USB device's MBR

# grub2-install --force --boot-directory=/run/media/dude/DT200/boot /dev/sdd

Copy over the grub.cfg file as well as the theme it uses

# rsync -avP grub2/ /run/media/dude/DT200/boot/grub2

Now create and populate the boot/files/ and iso/ directories. Example :

/mnt/boot/files:
sysrescd

/mnt/iso:
gparted-live-0.14.0-1.iso
ipxe.iso
rhel-server-6.3-x86_64-boot.iso
systemrescuecd-x86-3.0.0.iso
ubuntu-12.04-desktop-amd64.iso
ubuntu-12.04-desktop-i386.iso

For Fedora Live ISOs to work without extracting their content, see :
https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=650672
https://gist.github.com/2132076

./fedora-fromiso /mnt/iso/Fedora-17-i686-Live-Desktop.iso /mnt/boot/files/Fedora-17-i686-initrd.img

